alified because no multi-agentic-step correctness requirement is stated.","test_description":"Execute the full scheduled report pipeline against real delivery infrastructure (or production-like SMTP/API + real mailbox), then verify the message is received in the configured inbox with expected report artifacts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.9,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","required_reality_check_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is state handoff across modules/runs: delivery failure handling, local persistence, and retry orchestration. This can be validated with real filesystem + controlled failing mail adapter in-process (Integration). Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified because behavior does not require proving real network outage semantics or external inbox readback, only fallback persistence and retry attempt; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because no model-output decision quality is involved.","test_description":"Run pipeline with mail client forced to fail, assert report is persisted to expected local path; run next scheduled execution path, assert persisted report is loaded and a retry send is attempted (and cleared on success if configured).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.04,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.24,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
